Title : Wishart Island (British Columbia)
Text : :''This article is for the island in British Columbia.  For the island in Nunavut, see [[Wishart Island]].
'''Wishart Island''' is a small islet in the [[Queen Charlotte Strait]] region of the [[British Columbia Coast|Central Coast of British Columbia]], [[Canada]], located in the [[Deserters Group]] to the west of [[Deserters Island]].<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25540.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Wishart Island"]</ref>  Both it and the [[Wishart Peninsula]] on [[Broughton Island (British Columbia)|Broughton Island]] are named for a James Wishart, who was one of the crew of the [[Hudson's Bay Company|HBC]] vessel [[Norman Morrison (ship)|''Norman Morrison'']] who deserted that vessel and were killed on these islands by natives sent out to find and capture them.<ref>[http://apps.gov.bc.ca/pub/bcgnws/names/25494.html BC Names/GeoBC entry "Deserters Island"]</ref>

